The paper proposes a method for visual explanation of convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves optimization and defending against adversarial evidence, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses limitations and shortcomings of training data, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
